Articles.Content:
I'm assuming you are using steam. I would recommend:
a) Going into Steam Properties for KSP and verifying your files. To do this: right click KSP in the steam client application and select "Properties". Then Select the "LOCAL FILES" tab and then click "VERIFY INTEGRITY OF GAME FILES...."
b) Ensure you don't have any mods installed in your steam directory for KSP. Or if you do, ensure those mods are updated for KSP 1.3.

I appreciate the quick reply.  As mentioned in my post I already verified the game file integrity. The only mod I had was mechjeb. I removed that when I did the clean install. Neither of those made any difference.

13 minutes ago, jklier said:

I appreciate the quick reply.  As mentioned in my post I already verified the game file integrity. The only mod I had was mechjeb. I removed that when I did the clean install. Neither of those made any difference.

Mechjeb is not updated for 1.3 as far as I know and was causing crashes. Double check if it's updated. CKAN reports it as compatible but it isn't
It's also crashes with a clean install and no mechjeb.

16 hours ago, jklier said:

This is a MSI gaming system with 32GB of memory so that shouldn't be an issue.

The log says you run out of memory because you still run the 32bit executable instead of the 64bit one.
Sorry, I should have mentioned this in the original post. The 64 bit version crashes with the same error.
Same for me. But I have 12 gb of ram, so it shouldn't be an issue, never was the issue.

These are only things I can think of that have changed on my system since KSP last loaded successfully.

1. KSP update

2. Minor Windows 10 update from last Tuesday

3. Updated NVIDIA drivers

I'm going to try rolling back the NVIDIA drivers today.  As a test I may uninstall the Windows 10 update but that would just be a temporary test as I don't want to run with the OS not using the latest updates.

I rolled back the video driver and it loaded properly.  I then upgraded the video driver again and it still worked.  I assume something went wonky with the update last week.  I appreciate all the responses for help.
